    <summary>Specifies constants that define actions performed by the mouse.</summary>
    <remarks>
      <format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[  
  
## Remarks  
 The <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseAction> enumeration specifies constants which correspond to actions performed by the mouse, such as RightClick and RightDoubleClick.  
  
 <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseAction.RightClick> can be used with a <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseGesture> to create a input gesture which can be bound to a command using a <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseBinding>.  For more information about commanding, see the [Commanding Overview](~/docs/framework/wpf/advanced/commanding-overview.md).  
  
   
  
## Examples  
